window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>“A high-tech vampire epic....Terrifying.”<br>—<em>San Francisco Chronicle</em></p><p>“Part <em>The Andromeda Strain</em>, part <em>Night of the Living Dead</em>.”<br>—Salon.com</p><p>“Chuck Hogan is known for his taut thrillers, Guillermo del Toro for his surreal horror films…<em>The Strain</em> brings out the best of each.”<br>—<em>Minneapolis Star Tribune</em></p><p>An epic battle for survival begins between man and vampire in <em>The Strain</em>—the first book in a heart-stopping trilogy from one of Hollywood’s most inventive storytellers and a critically acclaimed thriller writer. Guillermo del Toro, the genius director of the Academy Award-winning <em>Pan’s Labyrinth</em> and <em>Hellboy</em>, and Hammett Award-winning author Chuck Hogan have joined forces to boldly reinvent the vampire novel. Brilliant, blood-chilling, and unputdownable, <em>The Strain</em> is a nightmare of the first order.<br></p>"; 
